subSubSection.paragraph:
As the lab-reared larvae we studied were collected near the emergence period of adults, the 3rd instar larvae were fed only once. After about 10–38 days the 3rd instar larvae began to spin a spherical cocoon covered by a layer of sand and other detritus for pupation; the cocoon was firmly attached to rock (
Fig. 11
). After about 15–42 days, adults emerged, which usually took place after nightfall.
